cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about text summarization using neural models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses specific architectural choices and pre-training techniques to improve performance, which suggests that it may fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of auto-encoders and neural networks suggests that it may also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) in the sense that it summarizes paragraphs into a single sentence. Finally, the use of neural models and deep learning techniques suggests that it may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
